Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.43,0:00:11.38,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,Umm, Mr. Rohan? {"Mr. Rohan" is what we used for the DiU BD batch -J}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.38,0:00:16.35,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,If you don't mind, I'd like to ask you a favor...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.17,0:00:22.43,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,What is it, Koichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.65,0:00:28.28,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,So, the thing is,\N I'm traveling abroad for spring break this year...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.28,0:00:30.46,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,Hmm? Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.46,0:00:31.88,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,I-Italy...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.41,0:00:34.15,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,Italy?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.15,0:00:40.01,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,Sir, will you please use Heaven's Door \N to give me the ability to speak Italian? {Unless it's too loose, suggesting "into me the ability to speak Italian" in place of "in me that I can speak Italian". - Toa} {not loose so much as a little awkward. I think this is fine. Could take an alternate approach: "Sir, will you please use Heaven's Door to write "I can speak Italian" in/on me?" -Jules}{Went with a hybrid approach and used Toa's suggestion minus the "write into" part. Asking him to use Heaven's Door makes that information superfluous -J}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.01,0:00:44.73,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,What would compel me to do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.73,0:00:50.28,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,I'm just nervous since this is \N my first time going overseas...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.77,0:00:54.35,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,I would feel less anxious if \N you helped me speak the language.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.95,0:00:56.01,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,Please, Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.81,0:00:59.87,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,You're going to Italy?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.87,0:01:03.37,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,I had quite the interesting\N experience there myself.{Literally it's "In that case I will tell you about the experience I had there", but that might be needlessly nitpicky on my part. -Starfish}{I think "In that case, " can be added since it only adds 3 CPS, but up to you guys. - Toa} {I agree that it's optional. If anything, it'll match the JP word-for-word, but it's not a big deal if the phrase goes missing. -Jules}{Opted to leave it out since the line isn't on screen for long. Even though the "I'll tell you about" part is excluded, I don't think it's necessary since this phrasing implies that he's about to tell him about it anyway. -J}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.37,0:01:03.93,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.45,0:01:10.71,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,Do you recall how my comic went on hiatus \N after that {\i1}punk{\i0} assaulted me? {He's referring to Josuke here -J}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.55,0:01:19.26,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,While I was recovering, I spent eight days in Venice investigating potential sources for new stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.81,0:01:24.14,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,It was there that I caught wind \Nof a curious happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.33,0:02:25.29,Thoughts,Rohan,0,0,0,,The episode I'm about to recount is one that I, \N Kishibe Rohan, heard with my own two ears.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.83,0:02:27.89,Thoughts,Rohan,0,0,0,,It is a record of true terror.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.00,0:02:34.09,Thoughts,Rohan,0,0,0,,Do you know what a confessional is?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.03,0:02:38.97,Thoughts,Rohan,0,0,0,,They can be found in every Italian church. {and American churches just have glory holes.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.97,0:02:41.58,Thoughts,Rohan,0,0,0,,Imagine them as two \Nside-by-side wooden phone booths.{Helloooooo, nitpicks! It's technically "which look like wooden phone booths." -Starfish}{Ended up going pretty liberal with this line. I don't think any important information is being lost here, though. I just added a bit. -J}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.21,0:02:48.52,Thoughts,Rohan,0,0,0,,A priest from the church enters the side \N with the curtain, and the penitent the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.99,0:02:51.90,Thoughts,Rohan,0,0,0,,The two sides are connected by a small window...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.90,0:02:58.53,Thoughts,Rohan,0,0,0,,...which is designed so that the priest and penitent \N are unable to see each other, but may still converse.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.90,0:03:07.25,Thoughts,Rohan,0,0,0,,By speaking through the window, \Nthe penitent is able to confess their sins in complete privacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.91,0:03:13.63,Thoughts,Rohan,0,0,0,,No one can hold secrets in their heart \N for years on end.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.05,0:03:19.13,Thoughts,Rohan,0,0,0,,The deeper the secret, \N the more the heart agonizes and yearns to cry out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.72,0:03:26.26,Thoughts,Rohan,0,0,0,,A confessional is where souls come to seek absolution, \N and embodies the knowledge of those who came before us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.22,0:03:30.35,Thoughts,Rohan,0,0,0,,Though it is forbidden, \N while the priest was gone...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.35,0:03:35.40,Thoughts,Rohan,0,0,0,,...I discreetly took photos of the confessional \N and examined its materials and engravings. {As discreet as a Japanese tourist in any foreign country can be.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.69,0:03:43.30,Thoughts,Rohan,0,0,0,,While I was there, I decided it wouldn't hurt to \Nconfess to a priest for the novelty of the experience...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.30,0:03:45.49,Thoughts,Rohan,0,0,0,,...and so I entered a box.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.49,0:03:48.24,Thoughts,Rohan,0,0,0,,Experience breathes reality into\N a piece of work, after all. {Ideally this would have been "breathes a sense of reality into a piece of work," to be consistent with the line this is calling back to in DiU, but the timing is too restrictive here. Oh well -J} {Rip. -Axel} {This is the better phrase here, tbh. -Jules}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.15,0:04:06.85,Main,Penitent,0,0,0,,Forgive me, Father, for I have sinned. {Orig.: Bless me, Father, for I must confess. This sounds like a set phrase, so I'm going with the English equivalent. -Jules}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.55,0:04:11.06,Main,Penitent,0,0,0,,It is a grave sin I have come to confess.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.56,0:04:19.15,Main,Penitent,0,0,0,,I can no longer bear this burden alone, Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.29,0:04:23.65,Main,Penitent,0,0,0,,I {\i1}must{\i0} confess. \NI've suffered countless sleepless nights.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.11,0:04:29.99,Thoughts,Rohan,0,0,0,,I swear I didn't know at the time that \N only priests should enter the curtained side!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.99,0:04:33.75,Thoughts,Rohan,0,0,0,,This man had mistaken me for a priest!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.76,0:04:35.71,Thoughts,Rohan,0,0,0,,Yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.41,0:04:38.54,Thoughts,Rohan,0,0,0,,...was this my lucky day?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.13,0:04:45.34,Thoughts,Rohan,0,0,0,,What was his "grave sin"? \N Listening to him couldn't hurt, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.34,0:04:48.18,Thoughts,Rohan,0,0,0,,{\i1}Experience{\i0} is what breathes reality \N into a piece of work. {Yes, this is more or less supposed to be the same as the previous one -J}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.90,0:04:51.64,Thoughts,Rohan,0,0,0,,It didn't really matter \N who listened to this man.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.64,0:04:58.40,Thoughts,Rohan,0,0,0,,Ultimately, it was more important that \N he believed he was confessing to a priest. {Added "that" -G}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.40,0:05:01.33,Main,Penitent,0,0,0,,Father, is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.07,0:05:06.78,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,Go on. Keep talking.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.78,0:05:08.62,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,I mean, please continue. {The idea here is that Rohan switches from insisting, informal Japanese to polite, formal Japanese. If the switch was only apparent after reading this comment, please let me know and we can workshop this a bit -J}{I think intent comes across clearly. - Toa} {Good line. -Axel}{You'll know when I ream you later on. ^^ -Jules}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.05,0:05:13.45,Main,Penitent,0,0,0,,Of course. Where to begin?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.45,0:05:16.75,Main,Penitent,0,0,0,,Well, there was that evening...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.75,0:05:17.69,Main,Penitent,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.42,0:05:21.64,Thoughts,Penitent,0,0,0,,This all began that fateful evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.22,0:05:36.89,Thoughts,Penitent,0,0,0,,I was twenty-four years old\N and working at a food market.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.89,0:05:38.52,Thoughts,Penitent,0,0,0,,I did manual labor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.77,0:05:43.28,Thoughts,Penitent,0,0,0,,I carried bags of corn and \Nloaded them into trucks and warehouses.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.69,0:05:48.95,Thoughts,Penitent,0,0,0,,It was grueling, time-consuming work \N that left me no time to have a girlfriend.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.95,0:05:52.74,Thoughts,Penitent,0,0,0,,I hated that job more than anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.75,0:06:00.70,Thoughts,Penitent,0,0,0,,It was already past six o'clock that evening, \Nbut as per usual, I was working overtime.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.24,0:06:02.88,Thoughts,Penitent,0,0,0,,That's when it happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.88,0:06:05.42,Thoughts,Penitent,0,0,0,,{\i1}That{\i0} man approached me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.30,0:06:14.56,Thoughts,Penitent,0,0,0,,From his hobbling gait, lifeless gaze, \N unkempt hair, and foul body odor...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.56,0:06:18.35,Thoughts,Penitent,0,0,0,,...I knew at once that he was a vagrant.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.35,0:06:22.73,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,Please, spare some food... {WHY IS THE FACE NOT ANIMATED AT ALL! ONLY THE MOUTH! AAAH -Gyro}{I dunno, but it looks creepy as fuck, which is probably a good thing -J}{Um... Since when was this in any way unusual or unexpected. This is anime. This kinda shit is VERY common, dude. -Starfish}{Usually when shows cheap out on mouth movement, the shading is more simplistic so it doesn't look this derpy. There were plenty of times when this happened throughout the show, but usually it was better disguised. - Toa} {Haha face go brr brr (kill me if I ever say "brr brr" again). -Axel}{ok}{reatard}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.23,0:06:25.40,Thoughts,Penitent,0,0,0,,He spoke with a feeble voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.40,0:06:30.11,Thoughts,Penitent,0,0,0,,I caught him stealing glances \N at my lunch on the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.55,0:06:33.28,Thoughts,Penitent,0,0,0,,A sudden anger came over me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.28,0:06:40.17,Thoughts,Penitent,0,0,0,,Here I was working overtime, while this man had \N likely just been loitering at the park or behind the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.17,0:06:44.34,Thoughts,Penitent,0,0,0,,Yet he expected {\i1}me{\i0} to give {\i1}him{\i0} food?\N What an entitled wretch.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.78,0:06:51.30,Main,Penitent,0,0,0,,I {\i1}work{\i0} for my money, \Nthen use what I earned to buy food. Why not try that? {I wanna see real-life Italians express themselves using this body language}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.66,0:06:56.31,Main,Penitent,0,0,0,,You can have my food if you load \Nall this product into the warehouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.31,0:06:58.02,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,I... I... I...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.02,0:06:59.69,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,I'll do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.69,0:07:03.19,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,Just please let me eat first!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.19,0:07:07.23,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,I've had nothing for five days! I swear! {he's just fasting bro, gotta shred}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.23,0:07:12.49,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,Give me just a little! \N I'll work once I've eaten! I promise!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.49,0:07:18.50,Main,Penitent,0,0,0,,Slow on the uptake, huh? \N You're not supposed to get paid 'till {\i1}after{\i0} you do the work.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.50,0:07:20.86,Main,Penitent,0,0,0,,So you good for it or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.10,0:07:41.44,Main,Penitent,0,0,0,,Hold up! Why are you taking\N just one measly bag? Over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.74,0:07:46.14,Main,Penitent,0,0,0,,You got an hour to get it done! \N Sooner I go home, the better!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.74,0:07:51.61,Main,Penitent,0,0,0,,Come on, hustle!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.61,0:07:55.32,Main,Penitent,0,0,0,,The quicker you work,\N the quicker you eat!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.77,0:07:58.54,Main,Penitent,0,0,0,,This guy's had it easy for way too long!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.00,0:08:04.64,Main,Penitent,0,0,0,,Guess I gotta be the one\N who whips him back into shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.31,0:08:22.31,Main,Penitent,0,0,0,,Hey! \NQuit playing dead and get back to work!{All credit goes to Jules for this very on-the-nose line. The literal is "Don't go slacking off and pretending to have collapsed!" -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.31,0:08:25.02,Main,Penitent,0,0,0,,It hasn't even been ten minutes!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.51,0:08:27.69,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,Playing dead...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.08,0:08:32.58,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,Do I look...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.58,0:08:36.07,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,...like I'm {\i1}playing{\i0} dead to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.83,0:08:39.41,Main,Penitent,0,0,0,,What the hell are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.41,0:08:44.29,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,My despair runs deeper \Nthan the blackest ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.29,0:08:46.63,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,And it's all because of {\i1}you!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.63,0:08:51.17,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,I'll never forget this!\N I know your face!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.09,0:08:55.59,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,You'll pay for your transgressions.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.59,0:08:57.89,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,I'll be back! {Arnold?} {if arnold were ever homeless in CA}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.89,0:09:02.15,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,Once your happiness reaches its peak...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.93,0:09:07.40,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,...I'll come back for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.40,0:09:09.48,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,You hear me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.77,0:09:18.00,Main,Worker,0,0,0,,Look! \N Someone collapsed under that bag!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.07,0:09:22.04,Main,Worker,0,0,0,,He's dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.38,0:09:24.91,Main,Worker,0,0,0,,It killed him!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.27,0:09:27.39,Main,Worker,0,0,0,,Doctor! Call a doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.13,0:09:29.51,Main,Worker,0,0,0,,Call the police! {holy shit, the mouth gape is right off the cover of In the Court of the Crimson King}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.27,0:09:32.92,Main,Penitent,0,0,0,,I had no idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.77,0:09:38.05,Main,Penitent,0,0,0,,How could I have known he hadn't really eaten?\N I truly didn't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.05,0:09:39.72,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,W-Wait a minute...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.72,0:09:41.76,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,Err, I beg your pardon... {Same deal as the first time Rohan spoke to this guy -J}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.76,0:09:46.77,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,Did you say that the vagrant \Nspoke to you after he passed away?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.77,0:09:49.48,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,Are you certain it wasn't a dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.48,0:09:53.86,Main,Penitent,0,0,0,,A dream? \NOh, if only it were so...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.86,0:09:58.53,Main,Penitent,0,0,0,,Father, the events that followed \N are what truly shook me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.81,0:10:05.08,Thoughts,Penitent,0,0,0,,From that day forward, \N an unsettling number of good things happened to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.08,0:10:07.65,Thoughts,Penitent,0,0,0,,I received an inheritance\N from a distant relative...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.65,0:10:10.04,Thoughts,Penitent,0,0,0,,...made money betting on\N soccer matches...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.04,0:10:15.01,Thoughts,Penitent,0,0,0,,...and all the land I bought with my earnings \N sold for at least tenfold what I originally paid. {This was originally "dozens of times more than originally," but describing money multiplying in that way is awkward and sounds bad, so I opted to go loose here -J}{ur awkward and sound bad}{no u -J}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.01,0:10:21.10,Thoughts,Penitent,0,0,0,,The cornflakes and corn snacks I created were picked up \Nby a major food company and sold beyond expectations.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.10,0:10:23.60,Thoughts,Penitent,0,0,0,,They even did well around the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.14,0:10:28.77,Thoughts,Penitent,0,0,0,,I hadn't even come close to having a girlfriend before then, \Nbut I ended up getting married.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.77,0:10:32.52,Thoughts,Penitent,0,0,0,,She was a former supermodel \N who took part in Milan Fashion Week. {Yes, the "Milano Collection" is known as Milan Fashion Week in English, apparently.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.27,0:10:36.44,Thoughts,Penitent,0,0,0,,I earned more money\N than I could ever hope to spend.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.44,0:10:41.16,Thoughts,Penitent,0,0,0,,At my current residence, \NI have fifteen servants and three chauffeurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.16,0:10:44.24,Thoughts,Penitent,0,0,0,,My inordinate luck held me at constant unease.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.57,0:10:50.62,Thoughts,Penitent,0,0,0,,Memories of that dead man \N constantly occupied a corner of my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.26,0:10:59.72,Thoughts,Penitent,0,0,0,,And then, my daughter came along.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.06,0:11:02.76,Main,Daughter,0,0,0,,Papa! Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.76,0:11:05.47,Thoughts,Penitent,0,0,0,,A darling little girl who took after my wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.11,0:11:05.47,Secondary,Daughter,0,0,0,,Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.99,0:11:08.43,Main,Daughter,0,0,0,,Papa, watch me! Ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.43,0:11:09.88,Main,Daughter,0,0,0,,Keep watching!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.05,0:11:17.99,Main,Daughter,0,0,0,,I missed!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.99,0:11:20.95,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,So close! You almost had it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.95,0:11:25.78,Main,Penitent,0,0,0,,Your eyes were closed, Madam.\N Try again.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.78,0:11:26.70,Main,Daughter,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.47,0:11:32.04,Thoughts,Penitent,0,0,0,,As I watched my daughter play at the park...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.04,0:11:38.46,Thoughts,Penitent,0,0,0,,...I carelessly thought, \N "I am so happy right now."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.78,0:11:47.51,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,As promised...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.79,0:11:56.19,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,As promised, I've come back!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.19,0:11:58.44,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,Back to get you!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.21,0:12:01.78,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,Madam?! Is something the matt{\fscx300}-{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.78,0:12:03.61,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,Shut it, old man!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.54,0:12:10.66,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,Don't worry.\N I'm just borrowing your daughter's body. {Disgusting. -Axel}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.66,0:12:13.21,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,Stop this! Please, stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.21,0:12:16.50,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,You're mistaken!\N Let go of your unwarranted grudge!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.50,0:12:18.67,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,Unwarranted grudge?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.67,0:12:23.63,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,You've enjoyed nothing but good luck\N for all these years, haven't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.63,0:12:26.72,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,Wealth, fame, family, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.72,0:12:30.14,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,You think you got this far on your own?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.14,0:12:33.48,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,I was helping you from \Nthe shadows this whole time! {It's really comical to imagine this guy manipulating the soccer match betting and snack sales behind the scenes. - Toa} {"the" -> "this" -Gyro}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.48,0:12:37.06,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,All so that once you reached peak happiness \N and came tumbling down... {tumbling down, tumbling down, tumbling doooooooooown - Anno} {Who's Anno? Who are you? Where am I? How did I get here? What's my phone number? -Axel}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.06,0:12:42.20,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,...you would feel the deep despair I felt!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.65,0:12:44.74,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,But y'know...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.74,0:12:49.62,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,The only reason I wanted vengeance \Nwas to save my soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.62,0:12:56.21,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,It'd leave a bad taste in my mouth \Nif you thought my grudge was unwarranted.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.21,0:12:58.59,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,I'll give you one chance!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.59,0:13:04.31,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,We'll leave it up to God \Nwhether or not my grudge was warranted.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.93,0:13:09.47,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,Let's put fate to the test \N and see if you still have a future.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.47,0:13:15.31,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,If fate sides with you, \N it means my grudge was unwarranted... {Typo: "grude" instead of "grudge." -AxeltotheStoneMothafuckin'009}{Feel free to fix these in the future, just leave a brief note and also laugh at Josh. -Jules}{god you guys are mean -totally not J}{This typo passed by at least one person before it was corrected. As such... STARFISH! YOU'RE FIRED! -Totally not Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.31,0:13:17.98,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,...and I'll disappear without killing you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.98,0:13:21.44,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,Your sentence will be handed down by fate!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.44,0:13:25.07,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,Well? \NYou gonna test your luck or what?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.07,0:13:27.87,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,I-I have no idea what you're talking about! {Reminder that this is the servant and not the penitent, which is why he's saying this. He had no idea about what happened to his master at the food market. -J}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.87,0:13:32.66,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,Fuck off! \N Do you wanna test your luck or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.66,0:13:35.58,Thoughts,Servant,0,0,0,,Why? \NWhy is this happening to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.58,0:13:36.79,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,Answer!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.79,0:13:39.59,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,I'll save me some time and \N rip your head off now if it's a no!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.27,0:13:45.59,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,I... I will! I'll do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.59,0:13:49.09,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,Do I even have a choice?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.75,0:13:51.06,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,Good!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.57,0:13:52.51,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,Take this!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.29,0:13:59.23,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,Fate can be determined from \N even the smallest, least significant things.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.73,0:14:05.03,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,You're going to throw a piece of popcorn \N higher than that lamppost, then catch it in your mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.03,0:14:06.86,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,Three times in a row!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.86,0:14:11.53,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,If you pull it off, \N I'll accept fate's decree and disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.53,0:14:13.70,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,You're using some stupid party trick to...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.04,0:14:17.58,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,I need this to give my soul some closure.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.58,0:14:19.88,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,Is that stupid to you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.05,0:14:23.38,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,Toss it when I clap my hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.38,0:14:27.97,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,If it doesn't clear the top of the lamppost, \N or you toss it too late, I'll kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.51,0:14:30.34,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,Ready? Here we go!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.34,0:14:32.05,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,H-Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.02,0:14:38.31,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,The height...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.96,0:14:40.27,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,Good!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.85,0:14:43.73,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,Why is this happening to me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.73,0:14:45.28,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,Forward!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.28,0:14:46.89,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,It's falling forward!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.44,0:14:50.03,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,W-Wait, no it's not!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.49,0:14:53.08,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,C-Can't see!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.02,0:15:03.17,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,That was close!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.17,0:15:05.50,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,But it worked! I did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.50,0:15:07.53,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,I made the catch!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.38,0:15:13.22,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,Second toss time!\N Grab your popcorn! {Now here's a good out of context line -J}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.22,0:15:14.47,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,W-Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.89,0:15:18.27,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,Th-The sun was too bright!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.27,0:15:20.18,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,I can do this in the shade, can't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.55,0:15:23.94,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,And what will you demand next\N if I say yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.94,0:15:24.64,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.65,0:15:26.69,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,We're doing this now!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.69,0:15:28.11,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,Right here, right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.50,0:15:30.82,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,Listen here! \NDo it twice more.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.82,0:15:33.57,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,I'll kill you if you fail!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.57,0:15:37.66,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,If you win,\N I'll disappear as promised.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.33,0:15:40.96,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,Now toss the second one!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.92,0:15:46.88,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,So you'll disappear for good if I win, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.63,0:15:51.63,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,You'll spare my life\N if I beat you, is that right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.63,0:15:53.59,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,Quit yapping!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.59,0:15:55.35,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,Toss it or you're dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.31,0:16:03.56,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,Yes!\N The clouds are blocking the sun!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.56,0:16:06.06,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,I can see it falling straight down!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.78,0:16:11.74,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.77,0:16:15.41,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.99,0:16:18.83,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,Now that's nice!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.83,0:16:21.92,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,They think you're trying\N to feed them or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.80,0:16:36.26,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,I did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.26,0:16:39.60,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,See that? \N I caught the second piece, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.09,0:16:42.68,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,Go to hell! \NThis is too easy! {Hell shouldn't be capitalized -J}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.68,0:16:46.27,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,I was scared at first,\N but now I'm calm and collected! {Says the guy celebrating catching popcorn in his mouth... -J} {It's not an easy job, cut him some slack. -Axel}{When life gives you popcorn I guess? -Jules}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.27,0:16:49.23,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,I got this! \NI got this in the bag! {Too on the nose? -J}{Just enough on the nose, I think. - Toa}{Thanks, I hate it -Jules}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.23,0:16:55.07,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,Save the celebration for\N after you catch the last one!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.08,0:16:56.78,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,Ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.78,0:16:58.49,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,You know it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.49,0:17:01.50,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,This last one will be easy as...{FUCK}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.26,0:17:15.79,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,What's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.30,0:17:20.26,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,You're the one who got \Nall these pigeons to flock here!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.26,0:17:27.56,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,You're also the one who spilled \N every last piece of popcorn you had!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.00,0:17:31.40,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,Th-This one piece...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.93,0:17:34.52,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,If I throw it higher than the lamppost...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.36,0:17:38.57,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,Get the hell out of here! Shoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.57,0:17:41.03,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,There's no food left for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.03,0:17:44.08,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,Here we go!\N It's the final round!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.08,0:17:45.54,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,Wait! Please, wait!{Suggesting maybe moving the start of this line to 0:17:44.08 instead. I guess it depends on whether you want to count his "uwah" at the start as part of the sentence or not. Could go either way I guess, which is why I'm leaving it as just a suggestion. -Starfish}{Seconding, but very much down to preference. - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.80,0:17:52.59,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.88,0:18:00.97,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,How's that?! \NYou think the pigeons will go for burning popcorn?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.97,0:18:05.18,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,You think they'll want to eat something \N covered in flaming oil?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.18,0:18:09.40,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,Yes!\N It's coming straight down!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.86,0:18:17.15,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,I can't see!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.15,0:18:18.61,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,Since the popcorn's on fire...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.17,0:18:21.58,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,...it's blending into the sunlight!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.35,0:18:23.29,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,I can't see!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.81,0:18:25.75,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,I can't see it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.75,0:18:27.77,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,Wh-Where is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.63,0:18:40.80,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,The verdict is...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.80,0:18:44.50,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,...my grudge wasn't unwarranted!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.89,0:19:07.58,Main,Penitent,0,0,0,,"So how are you still alive?"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.58,0:19:09.86,Main,Penitent,0,0,0,,Is that what you're thinking, Father?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.67,0:19:15.25,Main,Penitent,0,0,0,,It's for that reason\N that I've come to confess.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.25,0:19:17.46,Main,Penitent,0,0,0,,I can no longer keep this to myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.46,0:19:20.45,Main,Penitent,0,0,0,,I've committed a terrible sin.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.74,0:19:28.14,Main,Penitent,0,0,0,,That vagrant made me wealthy enough \N to possess whatever I pleased.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.14,0:19:34.06,Main,Penitent,0,0,0,,Wealthy enough that I could even find \Na servant who obeys my every command.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.06,0:19:36.40,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,Master...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.40,0:19:38.11,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,Get out here...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.79,0:19:41.82,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,Master...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.38,0:19:48.79,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,You can repent all you want, \N but that won't make my grudge go away!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.38,0:20:06.10,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,You lured me in with money \N and had me get reconstructive surgery...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.10,0:20:11.10,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,Your trickery led to such an awful thing happening to me, \N so now my grudge against you...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.10,0:20:13.35,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,...master...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.35,0:20:16.57,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,...can never be forgiven!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.87,0:20:23.86,Main,Penitent,0,0,0,,So you can even enter churches?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.53,0:20:33.00,Main,Servant,0,0,0,,When your daughter's happiness reaches its peak, \N I'll be back to take my vengeance!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.37,0:20:36.21,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,Don't bother with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.57,0:20:44.22,Main,Vagrant,0,0,0,,The only way we won't get tricked again \Nis if we watch this piece of shit day and night!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.82,0:21:02.65,Main,Okuyasu,0,0,0,,Whoa! {I don't think this is necessary to sub, but comment it back in if you disagree -J}{Would suggest de-commenting. - Toa}{Uncommented -Gyro}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.65,0:21:04.03,Main,Okuyasu,0,0,0,,Spooky!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.03,0:21:05.74,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,Okuyasu!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.74,0:21:06.82,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,Yukako!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.82,0:21:10.54,Main,Okuyasu,0,0,0,,Mr. Rohan, did all that shit really happen?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.54,0:21:15.04,Main,Okuyasu,0,0,0,,Hey, lady! \NGet me a tapioca milk tea!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.04,0:21:17.25,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,Is that why you interrupted us?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.25,0:21:20.05,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,Are you accusing me of lying?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.05,0:21:22.67,Main,Okuyasu,0,0,0,,Nuh-uh!\N It ain't nothin' like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.01,0:21:26.51,Main,Okuyasu,0,0,0,,But're you sure it ain't just\N some Stand users dukin' it out...
